moduslam.map_manager.map_factories.utils.get_elements(vertex_elements_table: dict[BaseVertex, set[Element]], batch_factory: BatchFactory) → dict[BaseVertex, deque[Element]][source]

Gets elements with raw lidar pointcloud measurements and assign to the corresponding vertices.

Parameters:

  • vertex_elements_table – “vertices -> elements” table. Elements do not contain raw lidar pointcloud measurements.

  • batch_factory (BatchFactory) – factory to create a batch.

Returns:

“vertices -> elements” table.

moduslam.map_manager.map_factories.utils.transform_pointcloud(tf1: Annotated[ndarray[Any, dtype[floating | integer]], Literal[4]], tf2: Annotated[ndarray[Any, dtype[floating | integer]], Literal[4]], pointcloud: ndarray) → ndarray[source]
Transforms points` coordinates to the global coordinate frame based

on the given vertex pose and transformation: base -> sensor.

Parameters:

  • tf1 – transformation matrix SE(3).

  • tf2 – transformation matrix SE(3).

  • pointcloud – pointcloud array [4, N] to transform.

Returns:

Transformed pointcloud array [4, N].

moduslam.map_manager.map_factories.utils.filter_array(array: ndarray, lower_bound: float, upper_bound: float) → ndarray[source]

Filters 2D array [4, N] with lower/upper bounds. If a column has at least one value outside the bounds, the whole column is removed.

Parameters:

  • array – array [4, N] of points to filter.

  • lower_bound – lower bound value.

  • upper_bound – upper bound value.

Returns:

filtered array [4, K].

moduslam.map_manager.map_factories.utils.convert_pointcloud(pointcloud: Annotated[ndarray[Any, dtype[floating | integer]], Literal['N', 3]]) → Annotated[ndarray[Any, dtype[floating | integer]], Literal[4, 'N']][source]

Converts a 3D pointcloud to homogeneous coordinates.

Parameters:

pointcloud – pointcloud array [N, 3].

Returns:

Homogeneous pointcloud array [4, N].

Creates a table with vertices and corresponding edges of the given type.

Parameters:

  • graph – graph to create a table from.

  • vertices – vertices to create a table for.

  • edge_type – edge type to filter.

Returns:
